ENTRY       EC 3.2.1.102                Enzyme
NAME        blood-group-substance endo-1,4-beta-galactosidase;
            endo-beta-galactosidase;
            blood-group-substance 1,4-beta-D-galactanohydrolase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Glycosylases;
            Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
SYSNAME     blood-group-substance 4-beta-D-galactanohydrolase
REACTION    Endohydrolysis of (1->4)-beta-D-galactosidic linkages in blood group A and B substances
COMMENT     Hydrolyses the 1,4-beta-D-galactosyl linkages adjacent to a 1,3-alpha-D-galactosyl or N-acetylgalactosaminyl residues and a 1,2-alpha-D-fucosyl residue.
HISTORY     EC 3.2.1.102 created 1984
